<subSubSection id="5DA66552FFCDFFC706F2FC99FD3DFC72" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="150336D9FFCDFFC706F2FC99FD3DFC72" blockId="5.[151,1436,746,1133]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC706F2FC99FED2FCAB" bold="true" box="[199,322,818,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC70469FC98FD50FCAA" authority="Cho, 2022" authorityName="Cho" authorityYear="2022" box="[604,704,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lukasi" status="new species">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70469FC98FDE0FCAA" box="[604,624,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70448FC98FD50FCAA" box="[637,704,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">lukasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC704F3FC98FCDEFCAB" bold="true" box="[710,846,818,845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3CFB57B0FFCDFFC704F3FC98FCDEFCAB" box="[710,846,818,845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in that the pronotum lacks spots and the elytral punctures are arranged in single almost regular rows. However, 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC7051EFCFCFC31FC96" authorityName=": Gressitt &amp; Kimoto" authorityYear="1963" box="[811,929,855,881]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kanfani">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC7051EFCFCFCAFFC96" box="[811,831,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70578FCFCFC31FC96" box="[845,929,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">kanfani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the long thin median lobe (greatly swollen in 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCDFFC70792FCD0FD9DFC72" authority="Cho, 2022" authorityName="Cho" authorityYear="2022" box="[423,525,891,917]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lukasi" status="new species">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70792FCD0FE2BFC72" box="[423,443,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC707FFFCD0FD9DFC72" box="[458,525,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">lukasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCDFFC70426FCD0FD0DFC73" bold="true" box="[531,669,890,917]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3CFB57B0FFCDFFC70426FCD0FD0DFC73" box="[531,669,890,917]" pageId="5" pageNumber="116" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
